net.objectzoo.delegates.impl

Class ActionAsyncSupport<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.objectzoo.delegates.impl.ActionAsyncSupport<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the ActionAsync's parameter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Consumer<T>, Action<T>, ActionAsync<T>

    public abstract class ActionAsyncSupport<T>
extends Object
implements Action<T>, ActionAsync<T>
    This is an abstract support class that can be used to quickly implement asynchronous actions.

    All asynchronous calls are executed in another thread and forwarded to the Action.accept(Object) method.

    The Executor to use for the asynchronous invocations can be chosen during creation of ActionAsyncSupport instances. If no explicit executor is given the a default executor is used. The default executor can be set using the AsyncExecutor.setDefaultExecutor(Executor) property or is created automatically by the AsyncExecutor.

    Author:
    tilmann

      • beginAccept

        public ActionAsyncResult beginAccept(Consumer<ActionAsyncResult> callback,
                                     Object asyncState,
                                     T parameter)
        Asynchronously invoke this ActionAsync with the given parameter value, callback and asyncState.

        Associated with each call to beginInvoke is an ActionAsyncResult instance returned by the call and given to the callback that can be used to track the status and outcome of the invocation.

        Specified by:
        beginAccept in interface ActionAsync<T>
        Parameters:
        callback - the Consumer, if given to beginInvoke, is invoked upon completion of the ActionAsync's invocation and receives the same ActionAsyncResult that is returned by the call to beginInvoke.
        asyncState - the asyncState is an arbitrary reference that, if given to beginInvoke, can be retrieved from this invocations ActionAsyncResult.getAsyncState()
        parameter - the parameter value for the invocation
        Returns:
        the ActionAsyncResult associated with this asynchronous invocation
